      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 mb-10">
        <div class="bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">What is the best IELTS prep course for beginners?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">For beginners, iTalki and See Guru offer excellent starting points. iTalki has community tutors available from $5 per session, allowing you to build foundational skills at a low cost. See Guru matches you with tutors based on your current level and target band, which is ideal for beginners who are unsure where to start.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">How much do IELTS prep courses cost?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">IELTS prep course costs vary widely. Self-study platforms like Magoosh start around $99/month. 1-on-1 tutoring platforms range from $5 per session on iTalki community tutors to $80 per hour for premium IELTS coaches. Comprehensive courses like E2 Language offer monthly plans around $30 to $80. Choose based on your budget and how much personalized feedback you need.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Can I prepare for IELTS entirely online?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Yes. Every option on our list offers fully online IELTS preparation. You can attend live video sessions with tutors, work through structured video courses, practice with AI tools, or take full mock tests from home. Online preparation gives you flexibility to study at your own pace while still accessing expert guidance and official practice materials.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Which IELTS modules are hardest to improve?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Writing and speaking are generally the hardest modules to improve without expert feedback. Reading and listening respond well to self-study with practice tests. Writing Task 2 in particular requires specific structure and examiner criteria knowledge that a qualified IELTS tutor can help you master. Speaking also improves fastest with live practice and real-time feedback.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900/40 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">How long does it take to complete an IELTS prep course?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Most IELTS prep courses run 4 to 12 weeks depending on your starting level and target band. Intensive courses can be completed in 3 to 6 weeks with daily study. Longer programs designed for self-paced learning can be extended to 6 months. Most learners see measurable band score improvement within 4 to 8 weeks of consistent preparation.</p>
        </div>
